From 1124e50013859c55e11939a3beafff49d9ee48b3 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: RivonClaw CI <ci@rivonclaw.com>
Date: Fri, 10 Apr 2026 18:08:51 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] vendor(openclaw): add browser lifecycle hooks for plugin
 integration

Why:
- RivonClaw needs to track browser session lifecycle (start/stop) to
  persist session state (cookies) across restarts
- RivonClaw needs before/after action hooks for future extensibility
  (auth injection, captcha solving, page preparation)
- Existing before_tool_call/after_tool_call hooks lack browser-specific
  context and proper timing semantics

Removal:
- When OpenClaw adds native browser lifecycle hooks upstream
- Track: propose as upstream PR after proving the design in RivonClaw

Tests:
- extensions/browser-profiles-tools/src/browser-lifecycle-hooks.test.ts
